Theory Notes for Explanation
1.	What is AngularJS?

○	AngularJS is a JavaScript framework developed by Google.

○	It extends HTML with directives and binds data to HTML using two-way data binding.

○	Useful for building dynamic single-page applications (SPAs).

2.	Form in AngularJS

○	AngularJS provides ng-model directive for two-way binding between input fields and application data.

○	Forms use AngularJS validation directives like:

■	required → ensures input is not empty

■	ng-minlength / ng-maxlength → validate input length

■	ng-pattern → validate using regex (e.g., email, phone)

■	$dirty, $touched, $valid → form state indicators

3.	Dynamic Forms

○	Fields can be generated dynamically from an array of objects.

○	AngularJS automatically binds and validates them.

4.	Validation Messages

○	AngularJS gives form states ($invalid, $pristine, $dirty).

○	We can show error messages dynamically when a user enters invalid input.

________________________________________
Example Program (AngularJS Form with Validation)
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>AngularJS Dynamic Form</title>
  <script src="https://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/angularjs/1.8.2/angular.min.js"></script>
  <style>
    .error { color: red; font-size: 14px; }
  </style>
</head>
<body ng-app="formApp" ng-controller="formCtrl">

  <h2>Student Registration Form</h2>
  <form name="studentForm" novalidate>

    <!-- Dynamic Form Fields -->
    <div ng-repeat="field in formFields">
      <label>{{field.label}}:</label>
      <input type="{{field.type}}" 
             name="{{field.name}}" 
             ng-model="student[field.name]" 
             ng-required="field.required"
             ng-minlength="field.minLength"
             ng-pattern="field.pattern" />

      <!-- Validation Messages -->
      <span class="error" ng-show="studentForm[field.name].$dirty && studentForm[field.name].$invalid">
        <span ng-show="studentForm[field.name].$error.required">{{field.label}} is required.</span>
        <span ng-show="studentForm[field.name].$error.minlength">{{field.label}} is too short.</span>
        <span ng-show="studentForm[field.name].$error.pattern">Invalid {{field.label}} format.</span>
      </span>
      <br><br>
    </div>

    <button type="submit" ng-disabled="studentForm.$invalid">Submit</button>
  </form>

  <h3>Form Data Preview:</h3>
  <pre>{{student | json}}</pre>

  <script>
    var app = angular.module("formApp", []);
    app.controller("formCtrl", function($scope) {
      $scope.formFields = [
        {label: "Name", name: "name", type: "text", required: true, minLength: 3},
        {label: "Email", name: "email", type: "email", required: true, pattern: /^[^\s@]+@[^\s@]+\.[^\s@]{2,}$/},
        {label: "Age", name: "age", type: "number", required: true}
      ];
      $scope.student = {};
    });
  </script>

</body>
</html>

